@startuml syntax-recovery
' Syntax-error recovery state machine for SyntaxRecoveryLayer. Scanning a token
' stream, each position may take an Insertion / Deletion / Replacement repair
' transition (gated by RecoveryStrategy and the per-strategy cost), tracking an
' open-bracket stack; at end of input any unclosed brackets are balanced.
' Correction tier = amber; final state = green double ring. Palette: docs/diagrams/README.md.
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam ArrowColor #607D8B
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FFF59D
  BorderColor #F9A825
  FontColor #102027
  StartColor #1565C0
  EndColor #2E7D32
}
hide empty description

title <b>Syntax-recovery state machine</b>  —  green marks acceptance (a parseable token sequence)

[*] --> Scanning : begin / stack = <latex>\emptyset</latex>

state "Scanning" as Scanning : read next token;\nupdate bracket stack
state "Insertion" as Ins : emit insertable token\n(+insertion_cost)
state "Deletion" as Del : skip token via <latex>\varepsilon</latex> edge\n(+deletion_cost)
state "Replacement" as Rep : swap token for a\nbracket-matched one\n(+replacement_cost)
state "Balancing" as Bal : pop unmatched opens,\nappend their closers\n(+insertion_cost each)
state "Recovered" as Done #C8E6C9 : parseable sequence

Scanning --> Ins   : [Insertion <latex>\in</latex> strategies\n<latex>\land</latex> count < max_insertions]
Scanning --> Del   : [Deletion <latex>\in</latex> strategies\n<latex>\land</latex> deletable <latex>\land</latex> count < max_deletions]
Scanning --> Rep   : [Replacement <latex>\in</latex> strategies\n<latex>\land</latex> wrong bracket type]
Ins --> Scanning   : token emitted
Del --> Scanning   : token skipped
Rep --> Scanning   : token replaced
Scanning --> Scanning : ordinary token\n(push '(' / pop matching ')')

Scanning -[#2E7D32,bold]-> Bal : end of input\n<latex>\land</latex> balance_brackets <latex>\land</latex> stack <latex>\ne \emptyset</latex>
Scanning -[#2E7D32,bold]-> Done : end of input\n<latex>\land</latex> stack = <latex>\emptyset</latex>
Bal -[#2E7D32,bold]-> Done : stack drained

Done --> [*]

note bottom of Bal
  Lower total cost = preferred path:
  cost = original_cost + <latex>\sum</latex> recovery_costs.
  Each repair is a parallel lattice edge,
  so all candidates coexist for later stages.
end note
@enduml
